                    <comment id="12598018" author="rpuch" created="Mon, 19 May 2008 18:50:13 +0100"  >Attaching a test (which is a Maven project).&lt;br/&gt;
AccessManager denies removal of any item.&lt;br/&gt;
Test contains two methods: one for removal of node (passes), another for move of node (fails).</comment>
                    <comment id="12649689" author="anchela" created="Fri, 21 Nov 2008 15:52:01 +0000"  >When moving a node using Session.move() the moved node doesn&amp;#39;t get marked as removed (as it would be upon Node.remove). Since the permissions are checked based on the state modifications upon save() only, the check for REMOVE permission is omitted.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
However: The same test being execute with a Workspace.move(String, String) would fail, as the BatchedItemOperations explicitely check for both: REMOVE permission on the target node and ADD_NODE permission on the destination parent.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
For consistency between Session.move() and Workspace.move() i would opt for adding the corresponding permission check to Session.move(). </comment>
